# Check all dashboard services
sudo systemctl status rpi-dashboard-*.service

# View logs (last 50 lines)
sudo journalctl -u rpi-dashboard-app.service -n 50 -f

# Stop services
sudo systemctl stop rpi-dashboard-*.service

# Restart services
sudo systemctl restart rpi-dashboard-*.service

# Disable autostart (keep service but don't start on boot)
sudo systemctl disable rpi-dashboard-*.service

# Remove services completely
sudo systemctl disable rpi-dashboard-*.service
sudo systemctl stop rpi-dashboard-*.service
sudo rm /etc/systemd/system/rpi-dashboard-*.service
sudo systemctl daemon-reload

1. Service-Datei erstellen (z.B. f√ºr weather.py):

sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/rpi-dashboard-weather.service

2. Diesen Inhalt einf√ºgen:

[Unit]
Description=RPi Dashboard Sensor Collector
After=network.target rpi-dashboard-app.service
Wants=rpi-dashboard-app.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=blubb
WorkingDirectory=/home/blubb/rpi-dashboard
ExecStart=/home/blubb/rpi-dashboard/venv/bin/python collectors/weather.py
Restart=always
RestartSec=10

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

3. Service aktivieren und starten:

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable rpi-dashboard-sensors.service
sudo systemctl start rpi-dashboard-sensors.service

Dann sofort mit deinem Command checken:

sudo systemctl status rpi-dashboard-*.service

Mybe starten:

systemctl start rpi-dashboard-sensors.service

